               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl1162-1">AMS, I, 120- 30 ; BHO, 150 et 151. Suhadii', I, 62-68. Cureton, Documents, 63- 85. R. Duval, "Les actes de Scharbil et de Barsamya", JA, 8• serie, 14 (1889), 40- 58, et idem, "Histoire d'Edesse", JA, 8• serie, 18 (1891), 384- 90. AB 10 (1891), 479. DHGE, VI, col. 944 (R. Janin). Vies des saints, I, 30 janvier, 615, s.v. Barsimee. Segal, Edessa, 82- 87. BS, II, 838- 39 (J.-M. Sauget).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">According to tradition, Barsamyā was an early Bishop of Edessa during the reign of the emperor Trajan and a contemporary with the Edessan martyrs Sharbel and Babai.</note>
